title: EMMA Electronic PY-1 PisdiYAUwot Guitar Distortion Effect Pedal
description:
[

QR Code Link to This Post

EMMA Electronic PY-1 PisdiYAUwot Guitar Distortion Effect Pedal
Beauty In Brutality
You may have guessed it already, solely based on the looks of the PisdiYAUwot, this beast was made for METAL! The gain stage is raw and brutal yet extremely clear and defined. The EQ options are staggeringly versatile to say the least. The sound? Earthshakingly awesome! Chords, fast runs and triplets stand out with a clear and potent punch. No more mushy wobble, just power!

Powerful and versatile high-gain pedal
Extremely tight and transparent attack - no mud, all metal!
Ultra-wide gain range - from low-gain to beyond high-gain
Highly intuitive control set - dial in amazing tones quick and easy
Top-mounted I/O
Handmade in Denmark
Untrue-Bypass switching - a super-transparent buffered bypass
The PisdiYAUwot is pure fire. It's lightning in a bottle. It's what every other metal pedal out there wishes to be. It's the sound of a tight and punchy high-gain amp in a box, ready to bring down the house on your command. The EQ section pots are optimized to work in interaction with each other, and the gain range is extremely wide. Turn down the MID a bit, turn up the HIGH and get that old school Pantera like scoop. Turn the MID up, the HIGH down a bit and the LOW up, and you get a very modern in your face mega power distortion. Want it more brutal, turn the GAIN down a bit. Want it more gritty, turn it up.

This pedal will bring speed, power and clarity to any metal guitar player out there.

title: Acoustic Guitar with Gig Bag, New Strings, Strap, Capo for Sale
Gibson Guitar 1959 ES-125TC
description:
[

QR Code Link to This Post

Here's a mojo filled Gibson ES-125TC from 1959. Featuring a Maple top, Mahogany sides, and an arched maple back. This Guitar has the original nitrocellulose lacquer finish, and is in 6/10 condition. The bridge is Brazilian Rosewood. The neck is beautiful, straight grain, quarter sawn Genuine Honduran Mahogany. The fretboard is Brazilian Rosewood, with Celluloid dot inlays. And it has a very desirable '59 spec neck, frets and original tuners.

The head-stock is silk-screened with a gold Gibson logo, the tuners are the original 3 on a plate Kluson Deluxe tuners. Tuner buttons are solid and good for many more years of playing. The nut is original and made from nylon. The frets have just been polished, and have 70-75% life left. The neck is slightly concave and the truss rod is perfectly functional.

The pickups are Gibson humbuckers and they sound beautiful and clear. The case is a Alligator-style Gibson guitar case and it's included. If you're looking for a golden age Gibson guitar without breaking the bank, this guitar is just for you. 1959 was a great year for Gibson guitars, now you have a chance to own one.

title: 1930 Martin 00-18
description:
[

QR Code Link to This Post

Extremely free resonance and response - all that you'd want from a great guitar like this. There are no cracks or repairs. The soundboard is Spruce with Mahogany back and sides. There are some surface scratches, dings, and wear from many years of playing, but overall in very good condition for this vintage.

There are 2 metal "plugs" on either side of the headstock just below the tuner plates (as seen in the photos). We have scrutinized these mysterious "plugs" under magnifying glass and have no idea why they are there. It does not seem to be one unit going through the wood from one side to the other. If so, it would show at that point in the bass and treble string slots. There is no indication of a repair or break in the wood grain where they are. If anyone knows, please let us know.

title: 1967 Marcelo Barbero (Hijo) Classical Guitar
description:
[

QR Code Link to This Post

Spruce soundboard, Brazilian Rosewood back and sides. Very Good Condition.

This is a really wonderful guitar with perfect balance, tone, volume and playability. It is what a great Spanish guitar should sound like in all registers.

Marcelo BARBERO (hijo), famous in his own right, was the son of the very highly acclaimed and famous guitar maker, Marcelo Barbero. The guitar was made in the famous Arcangel Fernandez shop at Jesus y Maria 26 in Madrid. It is signed by Marcelo Barbero.

The instrument was originally made as a classical guitar so the previous owner, a flamenco guitarist, had the fingerboard expertly replaced with a slightly thicker ebony so the action would be more flamenco like. It plays very nicely as a classical guitar and the fingerboard can be easily replaced with a thinner ebony to be a little more classical in feel as it was originally intended, though all who have played it, like it just the way it is. The installed tap plates can also be very easily removed for even more volume, resonance, and sustain.

It is in very good condition with some surface wear. There are no cracks or repairs.


This is a cash price and transaction and pickup must happen (in person) at Guitar Solo - 230 Townsend Street, San Francisco
]

title: Roland GR-50 Guitar Synthesizer
description:
[

QR Code Link to This Post

Roland GR-50 guitar synthesizer in very good condition for $95. You will need to provide your own guitar with a GK-2 pickup to test it, as I no longer have a GK-2.
Please provide a phone number if interested.
Thanks.


With a new slimmer pickup system and digital synthesizer engine based on the highly regarded D-50 synthesizer, Roland released the GR-50 Guitar Synthesizer in 1988. The GR-50 system featured Roland's new proprietary GK-2A Divided Pickup and 13 pin cable. Now users can use their own guitar with the GK-2A pickup system installed. The GR-50 can also function as a multitimbral sound engine. The GK-2A Divided Pickup has two assignable buttons and a volume knob that can be assigned to control chosen real time parameters on the GR-50 module.

The sounds of the GR-50 are based on the Linear Arithmetic (LA) sound system. Where by the structure of a given sound is based on tones broken down into pairs called partials . With a partial you can select to use a synthesizer sound which is like a conventional analog synthesizer or a PCM sound which is a sampled waveform. Deeper editing of the sound engine can be done with the optional PG-10 programmer but all editing can be done from the front panel.

The Gr-50 has 128 Preset tones with 64 user available and can expand to an additional 64 user presets with a memory card. The GR-50 is 3 part multitimbral when used as a stand alone MIDI sound module. 2 synthesizer parts and 1 rhythm part. Additionally there are 64 rhythm tones and additional 64 rhythm tones are available with a memory card.

In addition to playing synth tones on the GR-50 the player can also play additional MIDI synthesizers in combination with the GR-50's sounds or the external MIDI instrument(s). Complex layers of sound can be created with what Roland refers to as branching. Where by layers of sounds are spread across the guitar fretboard with each string having the ability to have split points and layers much in the same way as on a MIDI keyboard. Sounds can be played from selected strings that are on board the GR-50, over MIDI, or both. Additionally strings can also be muted and have just their guitar sound sent out through the guitar output or completely muted.

Optionally the user can control program changes and expression with the FC-100 foot pedal and EV-5/EV-10 expression pedals.The GR-50 can be played by older Roland Guitar and Bass Controllers by using the optional BC-13 Bus Converter.

Saturnworks Guitar and Bass Buffer Pedal
description:

QR Code Link to This Post

Why use a buffer?

With the rise of true bypass pedals, buffers sometimes get a bad name. Some players have come to associate buffers with tone loss. However, without at least one buffer in your signal path, you may be actually losing tone, particuarly your high-end. This simple pedal can breathe new life into your pedal--especially if you are feeling like there is "tone-suck" along your pedal path.



This small pedal can drastically improve your tone, and allow you to regain the natural character of your amp--even with a large pedalboard. I encourage you to check out this video that explains the nature of buffers while demonstrating side-by-side demonstrations of its benefits: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YOWeoizp4y0
]

The ASAT Junior II carries two Paul Gagon-designed P90 pickups, specially spec'd to deliver stellar tones in each position and with matched output for more truly usable rhythm/lead switching. No more fumbling with the volume trying to find balance between the P90s.

The Junior II features an easy-playing, medium-C profile neck with 12" radius and 1-5/8" nut width for a classic ASAT feel that greets the hand like an old friend. Add on Tone-Pros bridge/tailpiece hardware, delicious Irish Ale-finished mahogany body and hard rock maple neck with Rosewood board and you've got one versatile ASAT that effortlessly covers a wide range of sonic territory.

The Junior II has popped up before in short-run Custom Creations models made at G&L's Fullerton, California shop, but this is the first time it's been this widely available. On top of that, it's part of G&L's Tribute Series, which has been garnering rave reviews for more than a decade thanks to its solid combination of tone, quality and value.
